description: The Macallen Building, Boston's first LEED gold certified building. Boasting views spanning from Back Bay to Boston Harbor, this high-floor triplex offers 1,775 sqft with 2 beds, 2.5 baths, garage parking for 2 cars, plus a +/-400 sqft private east-facing with water. This well laid out home is ideal for entertaining and comes complete with high end stainless appliances, granite countertops, soaring ceilings, built in closets, and an overall contemporary finish.  A+ location next to Bostons best night life, Whole Foods, and only a short walk to the Harbor Walk to the Seaport. For commuting, Mass Pike, I-93, and Broadway MBTA Station (Red Line) are located right outside the door. The Macallen is a 143 unit association, has on site mgmt, is pet-friendly and offers 24/7 concierge, landscaped roof terrace with heated pool overlooking the city, workout facility, and movie room.
